Samsung Engineering Working on $6.1 Billion of Saudi Projects

-- B y   W a e l   M a h d i
-- 
2011-05-10T16:30:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/samsung-engineering-working-on-6-1-billion-of-saudi-projects.html
Samsung Engineering Co. is working on
13 projects in the oil, gas and petrochemical sector in  Saudi
Arabia  with a total value of $6.1 billion, said Chief Executive
Officer Park Ki-Seok.  Samsung secured contracts from Saudi clients worth $12
billion dollars since 1999, when the company first entered Saudi
Arabia, he said today in Jubail.  The Korean company wants to start in areas including
mining, water and steel in Saudi Arabia, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wael Mahdi in Jubail at
 wmahdi@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Stephen Voss  on   sev@bloomberg.net . 